en_493046_0	Salaries of Sri Lanka Transport Board employees will be increased.
en_493046_1	The increase will be effective from next month.
en_493046_2	This agreement was reached during a meeting the SLTB Trade Unions had with Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva.
en_493046_3	Following this decision, the Trade Unions that were launching a work stoppage had called off their strike.
en_493046_4	SLTB employees in several parts of the island were engaged in a strike during the last few days.
en_493046_5	They were demanding a salary hike.
en_493046_6	A special discussion on this issue was held at the Ministry of Transport and Civil Aviation Services today.
en_493046_7	It ws attended by all SLTB Trade Unions.
en_493046_8	During this discussion Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva announced that the salaries of all Transport Board employees will be increased.
en_493046_9	The Minister said that despite this decision, if trade union action continued other groups will be deployed for the operation of buses.
en_493046_10	The Minister mentioned that he was compelled to take this decision considering the hardships encountered by the people.
en_493046_11	Trade Union representatives expressed their gratitude to the Government for taking a positive considering their demand.
